<item>
            <title>[LU-16345] ofd_commitrw_read() can be passed non-existing object</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16345</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A client can get evicted during OST_READ&apos;s bulk, so the corresponding LDLM lock is cancelled and OST_DESTROY can get over the object. in this scenario ofd_commitrw_read() can meet non-existing (just removed) object. this is a valid case at least until &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16064&quot; title=&quot;RPC from evicted client can corrupt data&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-16064&quot;&gt;LU-16064&lt;/a&gt; is fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="73407">LU-16345</key>
